Use the standard library
This is how to rolling_max of numbers:
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that n is numbers's length
   When n is 0, then:
      The answer is result
   End when
   Remember that best is item 0 in numbers
   Add result to best
   Remember that i is 1
   Do this diff of n and 1 times:
      Remember that x is item i in numbers
      When x is more than best, then:
         Remember that best is x
      End when
      Add result to best
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is result
Now you know
>>> rolling_max of [1, 2, 3, 2, 3, 4, 2] 
[1, 2, 3, 3, 3, 4, 4]
>>> rolling_max of [] 
[]
>>> rolling_max of [1, 2, 3, 4] 
[1, 2, 3, 4]